Our partners

See Tickets
See Tickets is a global ticketing platform connecting audiences to live events, from concerts to theater, and supports both established and emerging artists by making performances accessible. See Tickets is the official ticketing service at Fifty Lab this year.
Ritcs Café
RITCS Café is a vibrant cultural hub where creatives gather for music performances, artistic exhange. RItes tere supperts emerging talent by providing a platform for musical acts, helping to cultivate a space where creativity and innovation thrive in the heart of the city.
Belgian Beer World
Imagine an immense public space that welcomes all, in the heart of the city, in the spectacularly renovated Bourse build-ing... In that same site, you can come aross the biggest interactive center about beer: Belgian Beer World. More than a mere museum, it provides a brand-new experi-ence. Not to mention the surprising archaeological site that you can visit un-derground. And there you have it; this multipurpose place is La Bourse.
Beurschouwburg
Beursschouwburg is a multidisciplinary arts center in Brussels, known for its bold and experimental programming across film, music, theater, and visual arts. It serves as a dynamic platform for artists, fostering creativity and cultural dia-logue. Beursschouwburg continues its mission of promoting innovative artistic expression at Fifty Lab by showcasing cutting-edge musical talent and connecting diverse audiences with fresh cultural experiences.
Ancienne Belgique
Ancienne Belgique is a renowned cultural venue in Brussels, celebrated for hosting a diverse range of live music performanc-es. AB has become a key destination for both emerging and established artists, ot-tering a program that spans genres and styles. At Fifty Lab, Ancienne Belgique plays a vital role in supporting new musical talent, connecting audiences fostering the growth of the international music scene.
Konbini
Konbini is an innovative digital media platform, known for its edgy tone and engaging content, focusing on pop culture, news, music, and social trends. Konbini highlights new talent at Fifty Lab, reflecting its commitment to promoting contemporary culture and connecting emerging artists with their audience.
Resident Advisor
Founded in 2001, RA supports the discovery of new music, artists, and events while highlighting the communities driving electronic music. Local scenes are the genre's foundation, where Dus and promoters begin, fostering creativity and connection. At Fifty Lab, RA celebrates the power of electronic music to unite people in spaces of joy and inclusivity.
Fooding
FOODING is a print and digital guide to all the restaurants, chefs, bars, stylish hotels and B&Bs that make up the "taste of the times," plus an annual awards list for new establishments, a series of gastronomic events, a tool that allows you to make reservations at some fantastic bistros, and an agency specialized in event plan-ning, content production and consulting...
Kiosk Radio
Kiosk Radio is an online community radio and streaming platform broadcasting 24/7 from a wooden kiosk in the heart of Brussels' historic 'Parc Royal'. The radio was founded in 2017 and broadcasts a wide range of music genres, from jazz to exper-imental, from rock to electronic music.
Bruxelles Enreprendre
Bruxelles Entreprendre supports the economic policy of the City of Brussels. Through its accompaniment, support and promotion activities, the organization contributes to the development of the City, to the commercial and entrepreneurial dynamic, to the animation and attractiveness of our commercial districts, and to the development of a quality economic
JAM
JAM is a public service radio station of the Belgian Radio-Television of the French Community. Jam broadcasts emerging artists and lesser-known tracks by established artists.
PlayRight
PlayRight is the social, cultural and educational department of PlayRight, the society for the collective management of neighbouring rights for performing artists in Belgium. PlayRight+ was created in 2013 to support the performing artists and defend their interests within the sector. We are happy to count them among our partners for Fifty Lab.
Conseil de la Musique
Conseil de la Musique is one of the Belgian structures that supports artists both in informing them about the music sector and in offering them opportunities to meet other people. We thank them for counting Fifty Lab among their partners.
National Lottery
The Loterie Nationale / Nationale Loterij is able to support Fifty Lab thanks to its many contestants. • They are happy to be able to contribute to events like this, with a balanced programmation. With their support, we can continue our efforts towards a more inclusive music industry and build a better world together.
Court-circuit
Active since 1992, Court-Circuit - Pôle Musiques Actuelles - is a federation of contemporary music venues, concert organizations and festivals. It works to professionalize its members, structure and network the music sector nationally and in-ternationally, and support emerging artists in Wallonia and Brussels.
Sabam For Cultures
Sabam for Culture is the social, cultural and educational department of collecting rights for the artist. It has been around since 1981 to support, promote and develop the repertoire of artists in all its forms in Belgium and abroad. Fifty Lab is happy to count them among its supporters since its inception.
Fédération Wallonie Bruxelles
The Wallonia-Brussels Federation aims to promote artists from Brussels and Wallonia by providing support to develop their projects professionally. The federation also helps events and the cultural sector as a whole. Thanks to it, culture can continue to shine in Belgium and beyond our borders. Fifty Lab thanks them for their support.
Région de Bruxelles-Capitale
Brussels Capital Region - The Image of Brussels enhances the reputation of our capital by supporting cultural events that address a public curious to discover Brussels from a dierent musical and cultural perspective. We thank them for their trust in Fifty Lab. We both love our city and our common goal is to make it shine beyond our national borders.
La ville de Bruxelles
The city of Brussels supports Fifty Lab Music Festival since its first edition. Always supporting culture in all its forms. The city of Brussels has welcomed Fifty Lab with open arms. It honours inclusive events that show that diversity and parity are part of the cultural sector. In that sense we share important values & ambitions.
Belgium Booms
Wallonie-Bruxelles Musiques (WBM) is the specialized music agency of Wallonie-Brux-elles International (WBI)*. WBI agencies play an essential role in promoting the international distribution and marketing of cultural operators from the Wallo-nia-Brussels Federation.
Wallonie-Bruxelles Musiques
Wallonie-Bruxelles Musiques (WBM) is the specialized music agency of Wallonie-Brux-elles International (WBI). WBI agencies play an essential role in promoting the international distribution and marketing of cultural operators from the Wallo-nia-Brussels Federation.
VI.BE
VI. BE is the support center for artist and music industry - from beginner to pro, from local to international. VI.BE strengthens artists in a healthy music en-vironment.
